    "Acceptance criteria define 'done' for a story and must be testable: each criterion needs an observable, objective pass/fail condition that engineering and QA can verify the same way. Subjective phrasing like 'feel fast and relevant' cannot be tested and invites disputes. The fix is concrete thresholds and conditions (latency targets, a defined relevance test set) that make verification unambiguous.",
    "Floe generated",
